# ~/.claude/.gitignore
# Allowlist approach per plan §10a: deny everything, then re-allow
# canonical config + skills + memory + plans.
#
# Rationale: blocklist is fragile — a future Claude release could drop new
# files in here that contain secrets or transcripts. Default-deny means new
# stuff stays out until explicitly allowed.

# 1. Deny everything by default
*

# 2. Re-allow tracked top-level files
!.gitignore
!README.md
!CLAUDE.md
!settings.json
!stop-hook-git-check.sh

# 3. Re-allow canonical directories (and their contents)
!skills/
!skills/**
!plans/
!plans/**
!memory/
!memory/**

# 4. Belt-and-suspenders: hard-deny common secret patterns even inside
#    allowed paths. If a skill or plan accidentally holds a credential, this
#    catches it before it ships.
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.key
**/*.pem
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx
**/*.token
**/credentials*
**/secrets*
**/*.secret
**/*_secret
**/*_token
**/*_key

# 5. Hard-deny things we never want in here
**/settings.local.json
**/.credentials.json
**/.anthropic*
